blog.name: distantee
blog.title: LTR...
blog.description: Sono la classica artista, a volte un pò orgogliosa, che scrive di sè, delle situazioni degne di attenzione e del suo mondo. Mora, occhi scuri, e mi abbronzo facilmente (anche se questo particolare non so quanto possa interessarvi), mi piace il senso dell'umorismo e la dinamicità nella vita. Adoro l'amore, anche se probabilmente non sono mai stata attratta da una persona a tal punto, una persona capace di risvegliarmi dal torpore, che io chiamo anche "incapacità di lasciarsi andare". Odio la falsità, l'egoismo e l'ipocrisia, al contempo migliori armi per molte altre persone. Amo leggere profondamente gli altri e vorrei qualcuno che sapesse leggere anche me. Se la pensate almeno per una piccola percentuale come me, benvenuti nel mio blog. *questo messaggio si autodistruggerà fra 3-2....

summary: What's your thoughts on the detective pikachu movie????
question: What's your thoughts on the detective pikachu movie????
answer: I mean I have my fair share of qualms about it, mostly about how some of the Pokemon look, but it actually looks like a great movie, so I’m really excited for it! From the trailers I’ve seen it’s hilarious, so I want to go see it when it comes out in theaters. I also adore Ryan Reynolds so yeah having him as Pikachu was a brilliant artistic choice. Well done.

summary:
Hot Take(tm) Movie! Sonic says eff cringe culture!
(P.S. I’m seeing a lot of people rebloging thinking it’s one of those...
body:
Hot Take™ Movie! Sonic says eff cringe culture!

(P.S. I’m seeing a lot of people rebloging thinking it’s one of those good/bad memes. It’s not. I made this in support of both Detective Pikachu and Sonic as a fan of series who loves both trailers and has been looking forward to the sonic movie since it was first hinted at in 2013. And as someone who greatly disliked comparisons between the two. Personally, I think it’s fine if you don’t like. I understand a lot of the criticism behind the movie even if I disagree. But, please as someone who’s been in love with this movie since day one, don’t reblog this if you are under the guise that I’m dragging one movie down to bring another one up. Because I am absolutely not.)

tags: why did they give him teeth
summary: I think detective pikachu’s designs for the pokemon work a lot better than sonic’s design because the pokemon are equivalent to...
body:
I think detective pikachu’s designs for the pokemon work a lot better than sonic’s design because the pokemon are equivalent to animals. It’s possible to make them look like cgi animals. It’s a little jarring for us, since we’ve only ever had cartoonish, anime creatures to look at, but it’s possible to make work. Also? Some of them are meant to be a little creepy looking! They’re pocket monsters!

Sonic though. Technically he’s a hedgehog, but like. There’s no way you’re going to make him look like one. There’s no way you’re going to make this cartoonish, big (connected) eyed, weird character into something that looks anything less that horrifying when ‘realistic.’ He’s supposed to be friendly and sarcastic and approachable but you cannot translate his cartoon design accurately to realistic cgi and keep those traits. It’s not possible. You’ll make an uncanny creature. God forbid they give him teeth.
